Ex1 Create Mocks and SetUp

1. Create a new test class named StockBrokerTest create a mock dependency for the MarketWatcher and Protfolio classes

2. Create a stub for the getPrice() method of the Stock class

3. Create a method that will create and setup a new StockBrocker class before each test. Also pass any mock dependancies that the StockBroker class needs



Ex3 Do some Testing

1. Create a test method that tests the MarketWatcher mocks getQuote() method and returns the current stock status and assert that it is not null.

HINT! use when().thenReturn method on the mock marketWatcher

2. Create a test method that tests the StockBrokers perform() method and verifies that the Portfolio mocks sell() method was called when there is a 10% gain.

